tip.text: Exciting flavours cocktails and really cool decorations
Really good melt-in-your mouth sashimi. Super fresh too. They give a thick slab of sashimi on top of handmade sushi rice. For the price, it's definitely worth it!
Best coffee in the area! Smooth, perfect temperature, no sour aftertaste coffee!! The range of desserts and their flavours are always new and exciting !
Still my favorite ramen in Singapore ! Tried the seasonal special - tan tan. The broth is special and tasty - almost like authentic tan tan !
I Got the famous cold brew and black coffee. It's slightly sour - not exactly my taste but I do know of people who appreciate sour coffees! Texture is smooth though
The space is really small - but the decoration is cute and lively !
Dessert and sweets !
Glad that I finally got to try it !!
In love with their cake selection !
The aglio olio is not bad here ! Texture is 8/10.
Tried the calzone, pita pockets, al funghi, mushroom bake & charcoal tagliatelle for mains. I liked pita pockets the most! It's very rich in flavour and I didn't feel that I was lacking meat at all.
Tried all 4 kinds of soup - the western soups are rich in flavour and texture! The Chinese soups contain no MSG and taste really good too :)
The vegetables and fruits are very fresh - and the dips are amazing !
Had the king ramen and autumn ramen - ramen is good for it's price! The texture is good and there's free egg and free beansprouts ! Serving is super fast !
Tried the gula melaka cake and double shot latte this time, the cake is moist and the Gula Melaka goes surprisingly well with almond flakes. It's not one of those extremely sweet cakes as well !
The atmosphere is great, very pretty decoration inside according to the different seasons - a completely match with their theme of having different ramen for each season!
Their fried chicken used to be my favorite but the batter changed so it wasn't as tasty / crispy anymore ! But the beef rocket burger is good :)

formattedAddress: #02-01, Cluny Court (501 Bukit Timah Rd (next to Serene Centre))
location.crossStreet: 501 Bukit Timah Rd (next to Serene Centre)

tip.text: Great pizza and good atmosphere ! Had the salmon and Classic Italian- very tasty and crispy crust !
Sweet potato latte - again !
Tried the earl grey cheesecake - it's special, moist, and very distinct taste of earl grey!
Delicious ramen and very rich soup base ! You can ask for harder ramen texture as well.
Very good coffee!
Great place! Don't actually need to queue but be sure to go there earlier on sashimi discount nights !!!!!
Very good cakes and unique selection of tea - but the price is on the higher end - $9.80 / cake ! Love the decor though :)
Maki San - my alternative to subway !!
The atmosphere is great for catching up with friends, or spending some time alone playing puzzles! The cakes are very delectable and tea is rich in flavour! Time flies when you're in this cafe!

formattedAddress: 辛亥路一段136號 (新生南路三段)

tip.text: The bagels are to die for! Very soft and come in unique flavours. The soya bean milk is also excellent. The world got a whole lot better when you know that it's refillable! The ingredients are fresh
Lowercase - good place for studying/ catching up ! No wifi though
Love their sweet potato latte and their pasta is more on the buttery side but very tasty. Very friendly service as well.. Will definitely visit again !
Love the atmosphere and the chicken pasta !
